      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1"><a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a><span class="mx-1">›</span><span class="text-gray-300">Online Scrabble</span></nav>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Playing Scrabble on Mobile — Tips & Apps</h1>
      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400"><time datetime="2026-06-14">June 14, 2026</time><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span><span>8 min read</span><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span><a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a></div>
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">Mobile devices have transformed Scrabble from a board-game-night activity into something you can enjoy anywhere, anytime. Whether you are commuting, waiting for an appointment, or relaxing on the sofa, a few taps put you into a game against opponents worldwide. Here is how to optimize your mobile Scrabble experience for both enjoyment and skill development.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">Anytime</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Play when convenient</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">Turn-based</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">No time pressure</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">5+ apps</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Available on iOS/Android</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">Global</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Opponents worldwide</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Optimizing Your Mobile Setup</h2>

      <p>A few simple adjustments dramatically improve the mobile Scrabble experience. Screen management and app settings make the difference between frustration and flow.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Landscape mode:</span> Rotate your phone sideways for a wider board view. Most apps support landscape and it gives you significantly more board visibility without zooming.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Brightness and contrast:</span> Increase screen brightness when playing. Tile letters and premium square colours need to be clearly readable. Dark mode apps with high-contrast tiles work best in low light.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Notifications:</span> Enable turn notifications for asynchronous games. Disable other app notifications during real-time games to maintain focus and prevent accidental app switches.</p></div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Mobile-Specific Strategy Adjustments</h2>

      <p>Playing on a small screen changes how you interact with the board. Adapt your approach to account for the limitations and advantages of mobile play.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10"><p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">✓ Mobile Advantages</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Play more games in small time chunks. Turn-based format allows careful thinking without clock pressure. Can look up words between games for learning. Build habits through daily practice.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-red-500/30 bg-red-950/10"><p class="text-red-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">✗ Mobile Challenges</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Small screen makes board overview difficult. Fat-finger tile placement errors. Harder to spot parallel play opportunities. Battery drain during long sessions. Distractions from other apps.</p></div>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 The Zoom Habit</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">Before every play, <span class="text-white font-medium">zoom out to see the full board</span>. Mobile players often miss scoring opportunities because they focus on one section. A quick full-board scan takes 3 seconds and regularly reveals plays worth 20+ more points than your initial instinct.</p>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Using Mobile for Skill Development</h2>

      <p>The biggest advantage of mobile Scrabble is volume — you can play 3-5 games per day in small pockets of time that would otherwise be wasted. This game volume accelerates learning.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Morning commute:</span> Play 1-2 turns on each of your active games. The brief focused thinking sessions build pattern recognition over time without feeling like study.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Word study apps:</span> Supplement games with mobile flashcard apps for word memorisation. Alternate between playing and studying — 5 minutes of words, then take a game turn, repeat.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Post-game review:</span> After finishing a game, spend 2 minutes reviewing the board for missed plays. Many apps highlight optimal moves you missed — this focused review is where real learning happens.</p></div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Tablet vs Phone — Which is Better?</h2>

      <p>If you play frequently, consider whether a tablet offers a better experience than your phone. The answer depends on how and where you typically play.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10"><p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">📱 Phone Best For</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Quick turns during commutes, waiting rooms, and brief breaks. Maximum portability. Turn-based games where you play 1-2 moves at a time. Always in your pocket when inspiration strikes.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10"><p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">📱 Tablet Best For</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Longer sessions at home. Full board visibility without zooming. Easier tile placement. Real-time games where you need to think and play quickly. Closest to physical board experience.</p></div>
      </div>
